---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Privacy — DeviceLab"
  description="What DeviceLab collects, where it's stored, and how to delete it."
>
  <section class="dl-page-header">
    <div class="dl-eyebrow-hero">DEVICELAB / PRIVACY</div>
    <h1>Privacy policy</h1>
    <p class="dl-blurb">
      Plain-English summary of what we collect, why, and how you can
      have it deleted. Last updated: July 2026.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="dl-container" style="padding: 12px 16px 40px; max-width: 68ch;">
    <h2>Short version</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We don't set analytics or advertising cookies. There is no Google Analytics, Meta Pixel, or similar.</li>
      <li>We collect two pieces of data, both minimal: <strong>your email if you opt into price alerts</strong>, and <strong>anonymous outbound-click events</strong>.</li>
      <li>Your IP address is used only to detect country (via a Cloudflare edge header); it's never stored.</li>
      <li>Every affiliate outbound link is disclosed on the <a href="/disclosure/">disclosure page</a>. We don't share personal data with retailers — Amazon, Awin, and other partners see only the click that came from us.</li>
      <li>To request deletion of any data we hold about you, email us — details on the <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Who we are</h2>
    <p>
      DeviceLab is an independent device-comparison site. See the
      <a href="/about/">about page</a> for how it's built and funded.
      Legal contact: see <a href="/contact/">contact</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Track-price emails</h2>
    <p>
      If you use the "Track price" form on a device page, we store
      three things:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your email address (lower-cased).</li>
      <li>The device id you're tracking.</li>
      <li>Your target price (if you provided one).</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This is stored in a Cloudflare KV namespace (<span class="mono">TRACK_PRICE_KV</span>)
      with a one-year expiry. We use it for a single purpose: to
      email you once, when the device hits your target. No newsletter,
      no marketing. You can request deletion at any time.
    </p>
    <p>
      Legal basis: consent (submitting the form).
    </p>

    <h2>Click tracking</h2>
    <p>
      When you click a "Buy" or "Track price" button, we log the click
      event to a separate Cloudflare KV namespace
      (<span class="mono">CLICK_KV</span>) with a 90-day expiry. Each record contains:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Device id, merchant slug (e.g. <span class="mono">amazon-uk</span>), UI source (detail sheet vs. device page).</li>
      <li>Timestamp and current URL path.</li>
      <li>Active persona and category filter, if any.</li>
      <li>Your user-agent string, and the two-letter country code from Cloudflare's <span class="mono">CF-IPCountry</span> header.</li>
      <li>Your IP address, transiently, only to attribute the click to a country. It is not persisted.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      This is used to understand which devices and merchants actually
      convert, so we can prioritise the ones that matter. It is not
      shared with third parties. We don't build user profiles from it —
      records are per-click, not per-visitor.
    </p>
    <p>
      Legal basis: legitimate interest (understanding our own site
      performance). To object, use the contact form.
    </p>

    <h2>Region detection</h2>
    <p>
      To send you to your local Amazon domain (amazon.co.uk vs
      amazon.com etc.), we detect your country via the same
      Cloudflare <span class="mono">CF-IPCountry</span> header and cache the
      two-letter code in your browser's sessionStorage. It clears when
      you close the tab. Set <span class="mono">?region=US</span> in any URL to override manually.
    </p>

    <h2>Third parties</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosts the site and provides edge
        geolocation. Their
        <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" rel="noopener">privacy policy</a>
        applies to traffic they route.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Amazon Associates</strong> — outbound purchase links
        are tagged with our affiliate ID. Amazon sees the click; we
        don't share anything additional with them. Their
        <a href="https://www.amazon.co.uk/gp/help/customer/display.html?nodeId=502584" rel="noopener">privacy notice</a>
        governs the site you land on.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Awin</strong> — some manufacturer links are wrapped
        with Awin's affiliate redirector once we're approved for that
        brand. Same principle: they see the click, not additional
        personal data.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Cookies</h2>
    <p>
      DeviceLab sets no cookies. We use browser sessionStorage for the
      region cache and localStorage for a one-bit "you've seen the
      welcome hint" flag. Both are visible in your browser's
      developer tools and clearable at will.
    </p>

    <h2>Data retention</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Track-price records: <strong>1 year</strong> from creation.</li>
      <li>Click-tracking events: <strong>90 days</strong> from creation.</li>
      <li>Region cache: cleared when the browser tab closes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Your rights</h2>
    <p>
      Under UK GDPR, you can request access to, correction of, or
      deletion of any personal data we hold. Email us via the
      <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. We'll respond within 30 days.
    </p>

    <h2>Changes</h2>
    <p>
      If we change this policy in a way that materially affects what
      we collect or how we use it, we'll update the date at the top.
      Track-price subscribers get an email on any material change.
    </p>
  </section>
</Base>
